{{Nihongo|{{ill|Toyosukiiri-hime|ja|豊鍬入姫命|fr}}|豊鍬入姫命}} was a Japanese mythological figure and [[princess|princess]]<ref>{{Cite web |last=KansaiOdyssey |date=2017-07-26 |title=Oh Gods! The Tales of Omononushi |url=https://kansai-odyssey.com/oh-gods-the-tales-of-omononushi/ |access-date=2023-10-03 |website=Kansai Odyssey |language=en-US}}</ref>. She was the first {{ill|Ise Saiō|lt=Saigū|en|12=draft|12=draft}},<ref name="Saigū | 國學院大學デジタルミュージアム-2022" />

Her brother was the similarly named {{ill|Toyokihiribiko no Mikoto|ja|豊城入彦命|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|12=draft|12=draft}}

